name: Tumor protein p53
description: This gene encodes a tumor suppressor protein containing transcriptional activation, DNA binding, and oligomerization domains.

name: Epidermal growth factor receptor
description: The protein encoded by this gene is a transmembrane glycoprotein that is a member of the protein kinase superfamily.

name: KRAS proto-oncogene, GTPase
description: This gene encodes a protein that is a member of the small GTPase superfamily.

name: B-Raf proto-oncogene, serine/threonine kinase
description: This gene encodes a protein belonging to the RAF family of serine/threonine protein kinases.

name: Phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate 3-kinase catalytic subunit alpha
description: This gene encodes the catalytic subunit of phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase.

name: Phosphatase and tensin homolog
description: This gene was identified as a tumor suppressor that is mutated in a large number of cancers.

name: BRCA1 DNA repair associated
description: This gene encodes a nuclear phosphoprotein that plays a role in maintaining genomic stability.

name: BRCA2 DNA repair associated
description: This gene encodes a protein that is involved in the repair of chromosomal damage.

name: MYC proto-oncogene, bHLH transcription factor
description: This gene encodes a multifunctional, nuclear phosphoprotein that plays a role in cell cycle progression.

name: NRAS proto-oncogene, GTPase
description: This gene encodes a membrane protein that shuttles between the Golgi apparatus and the plasma membrane.
